Deusen weaves together traditional scholarship and a personal account of her travels through Siberia and contacts with scholars, shamans, and storytellers active in reviving traditional culture. Highlighting the importance of oral literature and music, Singing Story, Healing Drum guides the reader through the often confusing phenomena of the shamanic revival, both in Russia and abroad.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357151840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571518423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571518/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles